SECTION E - WHY THE FRONTEND VISUALIZATION LOOKS DIFFERENT
----------------------------------------------------------
1. FIFO keeps long low-priority tasks near the front, so urgent work can wait.
2. Priority scheduling moves urgent tasks earlier, so their finish times improve a lot.
3. In this workload:
	- Priority is slightly slower overall in makespan (50 s vs 49 s)
	- But urgent tasks finish much earlier on average (7 s vs 18 s)
4. This is exactly the behavior highlighted in the frontend comparison panel.


